headline: Tractor Supply (NASDAQ:TSCO) Misses Q4 CY2025 Sales Expectations
summary: Rural goods retailer Tractor Supply (NASDAQ:TSCO) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025 as sales rose 3.3% year on year to $3.90 billion. Its GAAP profit of $0.43 per share was 7.2% below analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Tractor Supply: Q4 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The average estimate of 12 analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of 46 cents per share. The retailer for farmers and ranchers posted revenue of $3.9 billion in the period, which also fell short of Street forecasts. Nine analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $4.01 billion.
